      "writtenOn": "2026-03-09T16:22:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It appears that VS Code actually has three possible values for its `git.autoFetch` setting[1]:\n* false - disabled\n* true - fetch the default remote: probably the one configured for the current HEAD branch, if any, or \"origin\" otherwise\n* all - fetch all remotes\n\nPerhaps implement the same here. Going through all repos and all remotes may be too much. This feature is potentially network-heavy for both client and server. With my typical workspaces having many git repos, some of which have even many (more than three) remotes I\u0027d probably never dare enable it.\n\n[1] https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/110811",
      "revId": "8a734e16478c6baf7d7f03ae11105d9fe03778c7",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
